09/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- A two-day summit of presidents and senior representatives of Southeast European countries, as well as international organisations, started in Tirana on Thursday (9 December). The summit on interethnic and inter-religious dialogue in SEE is held under the patronage of President Alfred Moisiu. 
In other news, Albanian European Integration Minister Ermelinda Meksi and EU officials signed a financial agreement under the CARDS 2004 programme Wednesday. The document stipulates the allocation of 58.5m euros to fund various programmes.
The same day, Albania and Russia signed a treaty of friendship and co-operation. Officials agreed the document would boost peace and stability in the Balkans. (Albanian News, news.bg - 09/12/04; ATA - 08/12/04)
